laboratory_examinations.findings: The non-contrast appearance of the liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands is unremarkable. A large 4 cm left parapelvic renal cyst is simple in attenuation. There is no ascites. An 11 mm dilated appendix demonstrates a mild amount of periappendiceal stranding without any evidence of fluid collection or extraluminal air.
Creatinine level is 9.1 mg/dL (Normal range: 8.4 - 10.3 mg/dL), indicating that it is within the normal range. No growth found in cultures.
